description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Community Audiology department is seeking two self-motivated Administrators/ Coordinators (full time and part time 22.5 hrs)who are able to work on their own initiative and to provide a friendly efficient customer focused administrative service supporting the Audiology Supervisor/Office Manager. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department provides a community based diagnostic hearing service for both children and adults and a screening service for all reception children within the Borough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be highly motivated &amp; enthusiastic with previous experience in an administrative role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have the ability to be flexible and possess excellent organisational &amp; communication skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have detailed working knowledge of Microsoft Office applications to include e-mail, electronic diaries, word processing, spreadsheets &amp; power point presentations. Knowledge of SystmOne software is desirable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have the ability to provide a professional service to staff, patients, relatives, &amp; carers at all times in this varied &amp; challenging role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working on your own initiative combined with the ability to constantly prioritise changing workloads is a must.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An understanding for the need for discretion &amp; diplomacy in a confidential setting are also essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we offer a supportive team &amp; a commitment to personal &amp; professional development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Mohammed Ayub – Office Manager on 0121 424 2339.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
